Text: The food ain't ready yet, you hear!? ...Oh, you aren't here for that? Apologies, I get people breathin' down my neck constantly, like they don't realize a proper meal takes time.
We'll need to shore up our supplies soon. When we do, you're welcome to any firewood you need. It belongs to everyone, after all.
The Garden of the Stars is a gathering place of sorts. Everyone in Iq Br'aax comes here to gaze at the night sky and hear tales about the stars.
I imagine it will become even more lively after the changes made for the rite of succession. There's a kitchen now, after all, and nothing brings people together like good food and good stories!
Living so deep in the forest, we are dependent on its blessings to survive. We try to never forget the debt of gratitude we owe, and strive to live in harmony with our surroundings.
Our knowledge of weaving has been passed down through generations, and I'm honored to be tasked with teaching it to today's younglings.
The dirigibles have brought many visitors from Tuliyollal, and I welcome them with open arms! I'm always eager to share our traditional weaving and food with new faces.
We've named ourselves after the br'aax, who rule over the forest. A fitting title for those who look over the woods and its creatures.
The woods are peaceful now, but eighty years ago this place bore many terrible scars of war.
Ahahaha! So you have come. Should you wish to further your training, you need but say the word. My dummies stand ever at the ready!
Come to see the reedbeds, have you? Be my guest. Just try not to get stuck in the mud.
If you have come to offer a prayer to Kixaihih, then please, proceed downstairs.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... How to fishcatch without being deepdragged or wetwashed away? Perhaps if Stowastiq ordered a floatysuit that let her waterwalk...?
The great stairs collapsing really is a nightmare. Goodness knows when or how we'll be able to secure passage back to Tuliyollal, nor if there'll be any profit to be made at the end of it.
I've got nothing to say to outsiders!
...Don't talk to me.
...Stop staring.
...Hmph.
...Go away.
...Sorry, but I can't talk to you.
Fangs are sharp, but delicate. In skilled hands they can cut as well as any blade, but they'll soon break if not maintained properly.
The equipment we make here is sold as far as Tuliyollal. You might've even seen someone wearing my work!
...I'm not allowed to talk to you.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... The secret to handhelping potsworn is to suremake that not only their workneeds are met, but their restneeds, too.
They need lots of tastyfood, plenty of sleepytime, and most especially, joyfun and happygames!
You were here earlier with Queen Sphene, yes? If you're from beyond the barrier, perhaps you know of a game called Triple Triad?
I used to play it all the time back when I lived in Tural. Why, it lifts my spirit to think back to such carefree days.

Lately I've been doing a lot of business with visitors from overseas. Considering trade within Tural is all but monopolized by the Pelupelu, I'll gladly take my small victories wherever I can find them!
Times like these, we must all endeavor to remain calm, for panicking will avail us naught. Instead, let us ensure that when the door to victory opens, we will be prepared to charge through it.
Nothing gets my mood up like playing games! And a good mood is essential to smooth business!
Competitions bring out our true nature. That's why they're so excitin' to watch─and terrifyin', sometimes.

I can't quite put my finger on it, but I have this sense that something is...missing. Life keeps getting in the way though, and I can never get to the bottom of why I feel like that. Do you know what I'm talking about?
Have you heard of Triple Triad? Seems like everyone around here's at least familiar with the rules. I may have to get my hands on some cards and try it myself.

Now that I've completed my field training, I'm checking our stock─not just counting it, mind, but making note of each item's condition. Should worse come to worst, it could mean the difference between life and death.
If there's anything I can help you with, please do not hesitate to let me know. It's my duty to present patrons with the highest level of service.
Business goes most smoothly when each party is in good spirits, and I will happily do my part to facilitate such dealings.
Merchants visit us from time to time. We offer them rarities only found here, while they offer us curiosities of their own in return.
Folk have plenty of theories about what these images mean. Some think they're a record of what our ancestors saw in their day-to-day lives. Others think they might depict another world entirely.
All I know is that my wife used to love coming here to look at them. That's the only thing that matters to me.
...I'm busy. Don't bother me.
Now that the crisis is finally over, we can all get back to doing what we do best─and for a Pelupelu like me, that means making my fortune!
There are fewer and fewer requests for relief supplies with each passing day. A sign of recovery, I think.
We've had no few travelers come into town lately trying to escape the conflict. I've only food and drink to offer, but I hope to offer them what comfort I can.
It's been a relief to see the mood has improved around here. Hope you'll come back again soon for a nice meal.
Welcome, traveler. If you require my scrivening services, you need only say the word.
Only one left... I really must do something about my dwindling stock.
Welcome, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. You'll be glad to hear business is brisk, in no small part thanks to your efforts.
As for our journey... Well, Uvlo is still gathering the funds. I offered to cover our travel expenses, but he is loath to be in debt to an elder.

It's been fifty years since I've left this city, so I've no issue with staying here a little while longer. While Uvlo readies his funds, I shall take my time preparing the shop─and myself─for the journey ahead.
There are no deliveries to be made today, it seems. Still, the shop must be cleaned and customers must be tended to.

I must admit I cannot count dealing with customers among my skills. I would rather stick to tasks which I can complete with my hands, but Master Shunye was most insistent I “get out there and smile,” as he put it.
He said friendly faces attract new customers... I think it shall be a while yet until I understand the subtleties of running a business in such a large city.
I wonder what Tepeke sees when she looks up into the sky...
Tepeke said she would spend time getting the lay of Radz–at–Han and speaking with its people. You will know her by the distinctive sword and shield she carries.
I hope Tepeke is in high spirits. May you both have the best of luck in your search for our treasure.
Nettse has traveled to the Pyariyoanaan Plain in search of information most vital. When you find him, please do remind him that he needs his rest.
Slowly but surely, my husband is returning to his former self. Once the treasure and Tepeke are returned to us, we can go home happily.
Oh, the unenhanced warrior! Keep it up, you're doing great out there!
\\<sigh> I had such high hopes for Black Cat...
Hmph, you again. Like I said, enjoy this feeling while you can.
Damn it all... How could you do something so cruel to a starlet so sweet?
Fresh juice, squeezed from locally grown fruits! Anyone? ...No?
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! People have been talking about my new menu, and I suspect I have you to thank once again.
Lately I've been trying to come up with new drink recipes, but Halnaruk keeps suggesting the most acrid ingredients...
Still, I'm glad to have him as my sounding board. Together, we'll strive for a happier, healthier Tuliyollal!
When not busy stuffseeking, Halnaruk likes to visit shop of juicymix. Spreading happyfeels to customers is worthy sweatwork!
Nostalgia is my twin sister. Like most people, we both used to wear regulators, but... Well, let's just say a lot happened...
Firearms make the most sense for people who don't have combat training like us.
That's why we salvage as many as we can from the mechanical soldiers, and convert them for our use.
Take care not to get struck by lightning out there. One fellow reckoned you could dodge them by jumping back the instant there's a flash, but that's crazy if you ask me.
Honestly, I couldn't ask for a better job. Fresh air, and I get to spend most of my day with these darling rroneek.
You'll do us the honor of riding the float at the next Ihih'hana, won't you?
Who will be the victor of the rite of succession? Who will claim the throne? It's all so exciting!
I'm sorry... I should have noticed sooner...
I hope Tentoawa thinks before he acts...
Tentoawa has traveled to Ishgard, and he's likely gathering information in the city's taverns.
You found Tentoawa? Oh, the narwhal guides us true once more.
While I want nothing more than for the artifact to be returned, I must ask that you be cautious. Even if you find the thief, think before engaging her directly.
With the threat of the artifact gone, I am pleased to say the reputation of the Temple Knights has recovered.
Of course, our reputation is a distant second to our duty. Even if we were disparaged, our shields would yet stand strong, and we would give our very bodies to the protection of Ishgard's people.
A guardian must protect what he believes in. A lesson well taught by you and Master Tentoawa.
By the Fury's blessing, we were able to settle the matter of the artifact before any of Ishgard's citizens came to harm.
This experience was a stark reminder that I must stand strong as a protector of the people─the very symbol of their safety. Only then can I give them peace of mind.
Netherling is always welcome in Ok'Zundu! Like summer rain after a long drought, your actions have brought peace to our village and set the hearts of its people at ease.

Although peaceful delegation was ruined, Ishgard and Ok'Zundu shall forge bonds with gifts and gestures of goodwill. Perhaps soon Sonu Vanu travels west to show appreciation to mighty Tentoawa and courageous Loazenikwe.
As you can see, only the finest leather for my saddles.
I've decided to keep that mezcal for a special occasion: the ascension of the next Dawnservant.
Ohokaliy!!!
...Hm. I would reproach your dearth of manners, but I see now that you hail from foreign climes. One cannot expect outsiders to be familiar with our customs...only that they learn them quickly.
Queen Sphene is so wonderfully kind. She's always willing to listen. In many ways she feels like family. I know it must sound ridiculous...
I can't believe the queen is gone... However will I break the news to Milos?
Got some time before my next meetin'─figured I'd give this Slithery Trivia Trial a shot. Heard there's a lucky li'l somethin' waiting at the end of the quiz too.
Claimin' something bestows good fortune─well that's hardly somethin' you can prove, right? But folks have been lining up to get their hands on a prize!

Which got me thinkin'. Clearly there's a demand for lucky bits and bobs─if I get the word out that my goods magically help with money woes, or somethin' to that effect, people'll happily hand over an extra gil or two! I'll be rakin' it in!
Those Far Eastern rice cakes look absolutely delightful! Apparently, they're hard as pebbles, though! I was expecting something squidgier, if I'm completely honest with you...
I also heard about a scrumptious treat called “rice pudding.” All these rice-based delicacies─it's an exciting new frontier of dessert discovery!
Well met. You're speaking with the mochi daikan! I must say, it's a delight to see all the interest this event has generated!
And I heard all about your encounter with the Great White Tsuchinoko! How auspicious!

Ah, I don't suppose I can interest you in some advent cakes? They can't compete with the squidgy serpent itself when it comes to fortune, but they're a good deal luckier than your average treat, that's for sure!
Worry not, the rest of us will keep our preparations moving along. You need but concentrate on finding Gulool Ja.
I hope Gulool Ja will be all right. Should he return here, we'll be certain to let you know.
We've managed to seal off access routes on all levels. Any remaining soldiers should be contained now.
We couldn't have done it without you and yours out there fighting. Thank you.
We'll provide all the support we can. Please be careful out there.
I was living a life of excesses, bound for an early grave, when Cahciua came along. Though I was a complete stranger, she took me under her wing and set me straight.
It was out of gratitude that I joined Oblivion, but I can't imagine any other life now. I owe her everything I have, and it pains me that I couldn't say good-bye...
Uh... Ah...
I miss...Queen Sphene...
Sorry, but I'm afraid I can't let you through. It's much too dangerous.
No one's allowed through until we're certain it's safe. No exceptions.
Then it's settled─the Dawnservant Dedication Day Discount is hereby in effect!
The First Promise's golden alpaca is as spirited as ever. Too spirited, if you ask me.
I hope Dawnservant Koana will join us for Ihih'hana as well.
I must pay my respects to Gulool Ja Ja, though he will doubtless insist upon a bout...
Before the ceremony, we perused the Tuliyollal Saga on Morrow's Measure. I am proud to see Yok Huy glyphic traditions so prominently displayed in the city.
Pfffkohhh... Rakorok is excited to see how the new Dawnservants will handhelp Tuliyollal. This city will be as one big happypot!
I've heard there's another shop that serves delicious tacos. I'd love to try them...
More than a few of Mamook's citizens have expressed new interest in moving to Tuliyollal. I will confer with Dawnservant Koana to ensure their transition is a smooth one.
My apologies, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>, but we've no vacancies at present.
I have something to show you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Behold this white tsuchinoko ornament I won just moments ago!
See how it gleams with the same splendorous white as my fur? I cannot help but feel a keen sense of affinity.
Suffice it to say, the ornament shall have pride of place in my humble abode. I trust you will treat your newfound friend with the same reverence.
Right, we've got work to be getting on with ourselves!
Of course, the professor continues to plumb the depths of the aetherial sea, but naturally he also wishes to gain a deeper understanding of what happened in Pandæmonium.
This means uncovering what secrets might still lie within the Heart of Sabik. Of particular interest is ascertaining whether it can yet magnify one's ambitions.
The professor has been quite anxious since you left─I suspect he's worried about how Erichthonios will respond to the mammet.

Oh hello, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I must admit, I am still in shock after what Eutrope revealed to us... But Yaana and I will endeavor to find an alternative cure for the disease as quickly as we can.
Ah, speaking of Eutrope, have you ever found it strange that her name is so different from ours?
It's because she decided to change hers from the one our parents gave us to an Alexandrian name instead. Her progressive ideals are not limited to her ring persona─they are core to who she is.
Hey, it's the light-heavyweight champion! I knew you were amazing, but even I didn't think you would be able to take down Wicked Thunder. You truly are unstoppable!
I only wish I had been able to watch the match in person. It's a shame there weren't any seats, but I was cheering you on from afar!
Gosh, now I can hardly wait to see how you perform in the cruiserweight division!
A talented fighter and a brilliant scientist, Wicked Thunder actually fashioned her ring herself, using electrope.
The city within was born from her imagination and recreated with holograms. In such a space, she can easily wield her lightning techniques with reckless abandon.
Which makes the fact that she lost to you all the worse. Ugh, both those sisters are disappointments!
Well, if it ain't the new blood! Now's my chance to claim vengeance for the Brute Bomber!
...I jest. He's been too lax ever since his crowning. Far as I'm concerned, you rightfully put him in his place.
With this loss, no doubt he'll be inspired with even dirtier tricks he can use to make a comeback!
Just so you know, Honey B. isn't solely an Arcadion fighter.
She also stars in concerts as a songstress, and even receives work as a model for advertisements!
Sh-She was just so tired from all of her responsibilities that she ended up losing to you. It was out of her control!
Oh, it's you! I'm definitely starting to get the hang of this whole helping mortals lark─hells, I think I'm enjoying myself!
As you can see, I'm having no trouble earning myself a cookie or two. Now, if you don't mind, I'm in the middle of a show. Do me a favor and go bother Philcox instead.
Welcome to the For'ard Cabins, good <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>. While I am still in training, I will endeavor to ensure that your stay with us is comfortable.
Eh? What are you doing here? Apologies, but this area is restricted. If you've come to tour the facilities, please go somewhere else.
Heh heh heh... I trust you will do everything in your power to assist Philcox in his endeavors.
I'm visiting from Luwateninyawawsa to see my grandson. I hope he's doing well...
Please look after my grandson, won't you?
Oh, do you play Triple Triad? I hear it's popular overseas, so I taught myself how to play in case it might help my Eorzean clientele feel more at home.
I could go for a quick match right now, if you're up for it!
Hee hee! I'm pretty good at it, don't you think? One might even say I was born to play... No? Just me?
Oof... It seems my strategy could use some polishing. Sometimes I get so absorbed in the cards, I completely forget I'm supposed to be on the clock─but that's what I like about it!
A draw!? Ugh... Well, these things happen─but I don't suppose I could talk you into a rematch, could I? I want to win!
Fancy a game of Triple Triad? It's become popular among my colleagues lately as a way to engage with folks from across the salt!
How's that for Turali strategy, eh? Preparation is key when it comes to cards─and sales, for that matter!
Aaargh, I lost! I think I'll keep my goals modest for today, seeing as luck's not on my side...
Nice match! There may not have been a victor, but I enjoyed playing with you.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Warsowok's potsworn is not only a craftmaster, but also a cardmaster. Always playing Triple Triad.
And always beating Warsowok... Need to playtrain more to be a good fightfriend for potsworn. Will lowlander playtrain with Warsowok?
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Warsowok wins! All his playtraining offpaid!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Lowlander is a cardmaster, too! Happythanks for playtraining. Warsowok learned a lot!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Samescales, eh? Warsowok needs to playtrain some more...
Triple Triad? Oh, I'm always willin' to play! Ever since a travelin' merchant introduced me to the game, I've been able to think of little else. I'm always cookin' up new strategies!
My strategy worked! ...Only barely, I admit. You're a fierce player, and I don't know if I'd win a second time.
I suppose I wasn't as cunnin' as I thought... But playing against a strong opponent is its own reward! That got my blood pumpin' as much as any hunt!
A draw, it seems. Still, that was a thrillin' match! I'm already thinkin' up a new strategy for our next bout!
You got time for a game of Triple Triad? It's all the rage 'round these parts. Only trouble is, I keep losing!
Haha! I won! Maybe I should take on someone else, and see if I can keep this lucky streak going.
Dammit, I lost... Looks like I still need practice. I should play a few hands around the saloon, see if I can up my game.
A draw, huh? Could be worse, I suppose. At least I'm starting to get the hang of it. Maybe we could play again?
Playing Triple Triad reminds me of an old friend in Tuliyollal. How about a game?
Seems like I won. The strategy my friend taught me worked wonders!
Hmph! You beat me! Still, your style's a lot like my friend's. I wonder if he's been enjoying life while I've been stuck in here...
A draw... You know, my friend would ask for a rematch right about now. What do you say?
Have you heard of Triple Triad? I'm an avid player, but I can't seem to find my usual partner... Care for a match?
Ha, that's my win. It's funny, I remember feeling this way before, but...hm. Strange.
Ugh, fine, I lose. The way you play reminds me of someone... I just can't seem to remember who.
Oooh, a draw. I'm sure I would have won with a different strategy, though... Care for another match?
Hey, do you play Triple Triad? It's supposed to teach you strategy, so I've been giving it a try. Mind playing a round or two?
Hehe, looks like my training paid off! Putting your mind through its paces really does feel refreshing... Like physical exercise, but different!
You win, you win... I had no idea strategists of your talent even existed. You've given me a lot to think about.
Now that was a match! Sometimes the best fights are those that end in a draw. Thanks for helping me improve my techniques, traveler.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... It seems it will still be a longwait before the bigstairs are fixed...
...But Swipostik is sureminded that our feathery friends at the clifffoot are doing all they can to fasttrack the backbuilding work!
I hear a lot of bad things happened in the capital while I was stuck here waiting for the road to open again. I never thought I'd say it, but I'm grateful the storm struck when it did.
I became a mercenary because I wanted to be strong like Zoraal Ja, but after hearing what he did to Gulool Ja Ja, I'm not sure I want to follow in his footsteps anymore...

They say there's strength and unity in adversity. After what Tural's been through these past few moons, I reckon we're stronger and more united than we've ever been. I may be but a lowly fruitseller, but I feel part of something bigger now.
Pfffkohhh! A new shipment of tangyspices has arrived from the bigcity, and goodtime, too! No longer will the people of Many Fires have to survive on tonguesaddening fare!
Looking back on it, it seems like the great storm was a herald from the heavens, sent to prepare us for all the many trials and tribulations that would follow in its wake.
Now that peace has returned to Tuliyollal, perhaps the capital might spare us some of the materials and manpower we need to see the great stairs repaired.
A thousand apologies, but the Flight of We Wingless is still closed for repairs. If you're traveling upriver on urgent business, I can only recommend you try a different route.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Even if a pot goes smashshards, its potlife is not over.
Shinycrafters can stick the potbits back together again with shinystuff, and make an even prettier pot!
Now that the messymuddle in Tuliyollal has upcleared, we're starting to receive a lot of asktasks for craftwork from the capital again.
Our potsworn need craftstuff, and it falls to us helphands to find it for them!
Vendavoq was heartwarmed to hear that the new Dawnservant is a doubleservant.
Everymobbie in Earthenshire knows that teamwork is bestwork─just look at all the wonderstuff the helphands and the crafthands build together!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Tempatriq is happyfeels that Wuk Lamat and Koana were fingerpicked to be the new Dawnservant.
She is sureminded that they will not tinkermeddle too much with the potpact.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... These have been hurtytimes for Tural, what with the dangerrain here and the fightystrike on the capital.
But we shall not let our trickytroubles downget us! No, we shall all work together to overstep them!
Pfffkohhh... Doledriq received a writepaper from the capital, which said that one of her closest sellfriends was hurt in the fightystrike.
Thankfeels, she is bettergetting now and has opened up her tradepost again. Doledriq will order lots and lots of craftstuff to celebrate her bettergetting!

I hear it told that while I was busy fishing, the people of Tuliyollal fought off an invading army. If my younglings ever ask me, “Where were you when the capital was liberated?” I don't know what I'll tell them...
Even as the recent crisis unfolded, I felt it my duty to remain here and continue my work chronicling the arcane arts of this region, that they might be preserved for posterity.
But now that we have a new Dawnservant, mayhap it would behoove me to return to Tuliyollal, to learn if there is aught else to which the palace would have me turn my attentions.
The reeds are in burgeoning health once more! We shall soon have our rooves repaired!

I'm sorting through our stock, seeing what we can spare for the capital. We may not have much─even less so after the storm hit─but whatever support we can offer them after what they've been through, we shall.
Like the first green shoots after a wildfire, trade between here and Tuliyollal is beginning to recover. We must see the stairs rebuilt soon, lest we incur the traders' wrath!
Thank you for your efforts to bring the reeds back to life. If not for you and yours, we Hanu would be as limp and lifeless as they once were!
Ohokaliy, honored visitor! Ok'hanu is in a festive mood of late─all thanks to the recent festival!
Ohokaliy! Would you like a reed dumpling? Since the strength returned to the reedbeds, every Hanuhanu for malms around has developed an appetite for them. The next delicious batch will be ready soon!
Wasn't the festival wonderful? We were looking forward to the Lifting of Wings for such a long time, and it didn't disappoint!
I hear that Vow Wuk Lamat and Vow Koana were both chosen as the new Dawnservant. With those two at the helm, I know that our ship shall be steered safely, no matter how choppy the waters may become.
Is it true that Wuk Lamat and Koana are our new Dawnservants?
Why, those two worked miracles in restoring our reedbeds! If only for that, they have my unwavering support!
Ever since the Lifting of Wings, the air seems to taste all the sweeter. It is the taste of life, I am sure of it!
Before, the breeze that skims through these treetops merely tickled my feathers. Now, I feel it positively dancing with joy among the leaves.

Thought I might take a trip back to Tuliyollal─catch up with some old friends, you know─but then I heard about the attack. By the sound of it, the last thing they need right now is another mouth to feed.
The Moblins up in Earthenshire have already started sending supplies. Feel like we should do something, too─just need to figure out what.
The reeds are in full flush thanks to you, traveler─and long may they so remain!
Welcome, welcome! Any friend of Wuk Lamat is a friend of ours.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... How can Stowastiq enjoy fishcatching without being scaryfeels about deepdropping or being washed away?
Perhaps the boatcrafters in Tuliyollal know of a means by which a Mobbie might happyfloat on the wetrun...?
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... All the potsworn are back to their healthyselves! The potpact lives on!
Erichthonios's face lit up when he mentioned you. I see how close your ordeals brought you three, and I expect time will do little to fray the bond you share.
I was surprised to see an individual of the Yok Huy earlier. I'd thought to offer them a hot cup of coffee, but they appeared to be in such a state of panic that I thought it best to refrain...
Now that the skies above are free from that frightful presence, I can enjoy a new blend from Ciblu's Coffee Grounds in peace!
Just moments ago, a Yok Huy came to inform us that Valigarmanda is on the loose. Grateful though I am for the warning, I was still surprised by the sight of the giant rushing towards us.
When Valigarmanda was loose, I had the opportunity to speak with a member of the Yok Huy for a little while.
He was so concerned for everyone's well-being, urging us to seek shelter should we feel even the slightest hint of danger. I had no idea the Yok Huy could be so kind...
I happened to catch sight of a Yok Huy visitor earlier. If only we'd had the chance to speak, I would've offered them a beverage to soothe their spirits.
Keen for a drink? We've mezcal and liquor from every corner of the realm to suit all tastes.
Wearing our traditional garments and mask makes me feel ready to take on the world.
Tobli bade me to quickly gather my belongings, but he didn't explain why. Has something happened? The caravans still aren't fully repaired...
Everyone seems to be reopening their businesses one after another─everyone except me. It's as if they were hardly affected by the storm. Perhaps I'm simply inefficient...

A Yok Huy was here earlier, looking quite flustered. Seems like I'd better hold off on drinking <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>this evening<Else/>tonight</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>tonight<Else/>this evening</If></If>.
I'm hoping to distill the finest mezcal around for when there's something to celebrate. I'll have to work hard to procure the proper ingredients!
The alpacas seem afraid... What could have frightened them?
Given how sensitive alpacas can be, nothing makes me feel more at peace than seeing them relaxed.
Tobli seemed frightfully perturbed when I saw him moments ago. I fear something awful has happened...
Welcome to Wachunpelo, my friend! It is a pleasure as always to see you!
Agave Jaws lies to the north. I would warn you to be wary of monsters should you head in that direction, but you seem like you can take care of yourself.
I have some stern words for whoever's responsible for scaring the alpacas. When I figure out who they are, I'm gonna let them have it!
This here is the Family Ranch where we raise alpacas. Their fluffy fleece, wiggly ears, and curious capriciousness are just the best, aren't they?
I happen to be quite fond of them─despite having been the target of their spitting on several occasions. That cold indifference of theirs is just another part of their charm!
The alpacas are behaving somewhat strangely... I've never seen them like this.
Have you spoken with Yavli yonder? He loves alpacas dearly, but the feeling does not appear to be mutual─not with this lot, at any rate.
I have to respect the man. Despite being spat on nigh daily, his love for the creatures hasn't dwindled in the slightest.
This is where we dry harvested coffee beans. We mix them by hand to ensure each and every bean is thoroughly dried.
When I think of the soothing cup of coffee these beans will one day become, the long hours we put into our work feel like they're worth all the effort.
Coffee plants must be grown in soil that is neither too warm nor too cold. For the sake of coffee cultivation, it's crucial that the climate and environment in Urqopacha remain stable.
To the west you will find Miplu's Mate Garden. Though mate tea is good for one's health, coffee can be enjoyed in a greater variety of ways. They both have their strengths, don't you think?
I enjoy my work here, inspecting shipments before loading them onto our caravans and seeing the alpacas set off. Knowing so many enjoy our coffee is a reward in and of itself.
Isn't Valigarmanda the great tural vidraal which not even the Dawnservant was able to defeat? That you were able to is most impressive!
I shall continue to innovate with mate tea to discover the most delicious blends. I wish for more people to enjoy it─and I wouldn't mind if its market value went up as well.
I received word moments ago that Valigarmanda has broken free, but how do I inform the guests of this dreadful development...?
Ah, if it isn't the brave soul who vanquished the fearsome tural vidraal. Thanks to you, Icuvlo's Inn yet thrives.
I visit Urqopacha regularly for my dealings, and am honored to receive such a warm welcome from the Pelupelu each time.
When they receive news concerning happenings outside these mountains, they are happy to relay it to me. Thanks to them, I remain aware of the goings-on in Tuliyollal and beyond while here.
Is it only my imagination, or was there a tremor just now...?

Welcome to Panaqpelu Retreat! It seems you've been quite active since your arrival to these parts. Should you ever feel weary from your travels, you are always free to take a dip in these hot springs!
That's odd. I saw a ripple in the water moments ago... Was there an earthquake?
I journeyed here on guard duty for a merchant who has business in Urqopacha, but his dealings are taking longer than expected. Fine by me─I'll just keep soaking in these waters.
I think I felt a tremor a moment ago. If a strong earthquake were to occur, I fear this place could very well collapse...
One may immerse their body in the heat of these springs whilst feeling the gentle brush of the wind on their face. In such a tranquil state, one's troubles begin to seem so trivial...
Some friendly advice, outsider: leave this land while you still can.
It is a relief that Valigarmanda has been defeated, but this is not the time for celebration. There remain many injured to tend to.
Though some semblance of normalcy has returned since Valigarmanda was slain, there are yet many who require medicine for their hurts.
Perhaps I should gather my stock of jerky in case we are forced to flee...
With so many injured, sorrow fills our hearts. Yet Valigarmanda is gone, and that is news worthy of celebration. When all are recovered, I should like to prepare a feast.
To think a day such as this would come... I must pray for the safety of all in this land.
From the moment I saw you, I knew you were no ordinary individual. Thank you, truly, for vanquishing the Skyruin.
I've been made aware of the ongoing situation. Leave matters here to us, and see to Valigarmanda!
It is paramount that we keep vigil at all times, as many an unnerving creature roams these mountains─though I am sure they would pose little threat to a warrior like you.
If the Skyruin should return here once more, what will become of these crops we worked so hard to see flourish...?
It is thanks to you and yours, and the Dawnservant, that I can continue to tend to my crops in peace each day.
No, this can't be... I must evacuate my family...

I am truly relieved that none of my loved ones were hurt─and I understand I have you and yours to thank for felling Valigarmanda. Know that I shall pass down your heroic deeds to my children, and so too will they to their own.
Damn it all... How could this happen?
To think I let that accursed two-headed Mamool Ja escape... \\<sigh> I am well aware other matters take precedence, but I struggle to stifle my anger knowing he goes unpunished.
For now, I must concern myself with Valigarmanda's present whereabouts. I hope we may count on your aid, visitor.

In the coming years, I believe Karryorzar the Gracious may become a place dedicated to teaching our young of the heroes who laid the Skyruin low. With its foul presence gone, may Tuliyollal enjoy years of peace and prosperity!
I heard an unbelievably loud roar moments ago. But such a sound could only come from... Oh no...
It is our duty to safeguard the murals left behind by our ancestors in this passage, but it is thanks to you and your comrades that we yet live and breathe to do so.
Argh! I knew there was something off about that claimant and his mocking laughter!
Hehe, we were just talking about you, little guest! The brave and fierce warrior who slew Valigarmanda!
It is a dark day for us all. I must send word to my merchant associates not to travel this way, lest they come to harm...

There were some peddlers who dreaded visiting us due to Valigarmanda's presence within Karryorzar the Gracious. When they hear that the tural vidraal is no more, I hope they can make the journey here with their hearts at ease.
I felt a tremor just now... I hope that is all it was.
Please do not hesitate to let me know if there's anything you require. It is our duty to provide guests the highest level of service.
Below by the entrance is my sister, Yuplu. If you need assistance with finding anything here, she will be able to point you in the right direction.
I cannot shake this creeping sense of foreboding... But I believe that it is times like this when we need to distract ourselves most. Are you of a similar mind?
Tuliyollal faces an age of turmoil. We must keep an open mind to new ideas─and what better way to do so than finding novel ways to play!

Under normal circumstances, this facility deals with work-related inquiries. But after recent events, our purview has...broadened somewhat. Currently, our most pressing task is alleviating the citizens' anxiety.

What was Zoraal Ja thinking? Not that there's any point in someone like me trying to figure it all out. About all I can do is keep the cocktails coming. It's times like this when folk need something to take the edge off, after all...
The way I see it, moping about won't bring back Queen Sphene. I'm gonna keep shaking my shaker, and make sure there's always a drink ready whenever folk get thirsty.
There always was something about the king that frightened me. Between you and me, I'm not all that surprised by the attack... Doesn't make it any less devastating, though. \\<sigh> I need a drink.
What are they doing letting a kid take the throne? Besides, I thought we were supposed to have two rulers. Ah, never mind the questions─that's what the booze is for, right?

Here, we manage the exchange of soul cells. In the wake of the attack, we are processing an increased number of transactions. Distribution of all souls, including those reserved for hunters, is currently subject to ongoing delays.

Due to the current state of emergency, the elevator network has been shut down. It is unclear when the system will be back online. We are advising citizens to prioritize their own safety before considering travel.
This is the elevator hall. Access is restricted for those without official authorization. Thank you for your understanding.

My fiancée's family got caught up in the attack... Thankfully, they had enough souls saved up to make it out alive, but they're still reeling from the shock. Gods, I can't bear the thought of them suffering like that...

I spoke with my fiancée, and she wanted me to find a job that gives me plenty of time to spend with her. Well, I just submitted my application. Not much I can do now but wait and see what the future has in store for us...
Apparently, the government is going to compensate everyone caught up in the attack. I haven't heard any official announcements, though. I won't be holding my breath, that's for sure.
The panic has died down, but it seems like it'll take a while to get the city back up and running properly. I know he's just a kid, but I sure hope Gulool Ja has a plan up his sleeves...
Despite all the death and destruction, the commerce sector is basically unscathed and open for business. A good thing too─if the economy crawled to a halt, this ordeal would be so much worse.

If I've learned anything from all this, it's the importance of positive thinking. So here's an idea: if we could start doing business with the world beyond the barrier, just imagine the benefits we'd reap!
People need a place to rest and relax─now more than ever. That's why I plan to stay open and keep the coffee flowing.
The way I see it, every cup that cheers a patron up puts us one step closer to recovering from this nightmare.

Queen Sphene would visit Mosaic from time to time─not to drink coffee, mind you. No, she just adored seeing our customers enjoying themselves. Honestly, the memory of her smiling face is all the motivation I need to keep this place going.

Good grief... I thought the king was supposed to protect us... My friends and family are all safe─gods be praised─but what about everyone else? My heart goes out to all the citizens who lost their lives.
It's such a heavy burden to bear at that age... I just hope Gulool Ja can find the time to relax and unwind every now and then.
I'm still alive. That has to count for something, right? Still, it's hard to find joy in anything right now. At least the plants are still here...

Apparently, it was Queen Sphene's idea to create these gardens. Now that she's gone, it's up to us citizens to maintain the facilities we've been given. That seems like a fitting way to honor her memory, don't you think?
I'm struggling to process what happened. I always thought Zoraal Ja was a firm but fair king. To think he was capable of such horrors...
I'm sure Gulool Ja will do just fine, but there's no telling what the future holds. Not that I'm particularly worried...
I mean, I saw the ascension ceremony in Tuliyollal─with someone like Vow Wuk Lamat invested in our problems, I can't help but feel optimistic for the days ahead.
Times like these are exactly why we keep careful records of everything! Now, the crates in the back are from Limsa Lominsa, and─wait, weren't those in the front? Ugh, now I'm confused...
Another day, another delivery. The crate addressed to Xbalyav Ty'e smells so good, it's making me hungry─but the shipment for Vollok Shoonsa takes priority, of course!
Nations from across the salt have sent good tidings and gifts to celebrate the crowning of Wuk Lamat and Koana as our new Dawnservants! It's nice to know we're building friendly relations.
I've gathered up all the unbroken crates I could find. Some are a little burnt around the edges, but hopefully their contents are all right.
This harbor connects us to all the other nations across the salt, and I want to do my part to share the beauty of our home with each and every visitor.
I'm not entirely sure I understand what just happened, but seeing as I made it through unscathed, I'm going to keep doing what needs to be done.
Now that the crisis is over, I'm just happy I still have a job to do!
If the new Dawnservants intend to treat with foreign nations more proactively, I foresee my job getting a lot harder. But I suppose I should be grateful to even have a job...
I'm glad some of the crates survived the attack. We haven't lost everything... We can still recover.
Now that peace has been restored, I'm going to make the most of it! These international shipments won't deliver themselves!
I never imagined Wuk Lamat and Koana would both win, but it's no less cause for celebration. Come, let's have a toast to our new Dawnservants!
Those...machines that attacked us─where did they come from? Is this city even safe anymore?
Heard you fought shoulder to shoulder with the Dawnservant. If it weren't for you, I might not be sitting here, enjoying these great tacos!
I often see Wuk Lamat eating tacos here. She may be our new Vow of Resolve, but it hasn't made her any less personable.
I'm glad none of us were hurt, but we mustn't forget to replenish our energies. It pains me to think of those who will never taste these tacos again...
A lot has changed in Tuliyollal, but I'm relieved that the flavor of these tacos has remained the same. For many, it's comfort food.
Times like these, I need to stay positive. If anyone can offer our community a place to forget their woes, it's me!

Go ahead, folks, order anything off the menu─<If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>tonight<Else/>today</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>today<Else/>tonight</If></If>, it's on the house! I'm even offering a special cocktail to commemorate the Dawnservant's triumphant return!
Looks like we'll have to replace the whole pillar. It was only a glancing blow, but the force of the explosion must have bent the damn thing...
Our new Dawnservants are going to take this country to even greater heights. I can feel my hopes soaring already!
Commander Zoraal Ja may have gone missing, but our duty to this country remains the same as it ever was.
What good is the Landsguard if it couldn't even protect the city? ...No, I shouldn't speak as though it's over. With the enemy still close at hand, we must remain vigilant!
It's hard to accept that our former commander is...well...he's their commander now. But this changes nothing. All of us who yet remain will continue to defend Tuliyollal in Koana's name.
That attack may have caught us off guard, but they won't be so lucky next time. We'll simply have to tighten our security.
In olden times, Hunu'iliy served as a surveillance tower to scan the north for threats. In light of the recent catastrophe, perhaps it's time we returned it to that role.
The Vow of Resolve really knows how to give a rousing speech. If she's committed to this, then we of the Landsguard will serve as her sword and charge forward to victory!
I think I'll put in a formal request to repurpose Hunu'iliy as a surveillance tower, like in the old days. We could use some eyes in the sky to keep the city safe.
If you ask me, it makes perfect sense to divide the title of Dawnservant between two rulers. The only difference is that this time, they'll have two bodies as well.
For all the training I did, I never expected to actually need it. So when I saw those things right in front of me, I...I froze up, damn it all!
Peace was a privilege I took for granted. After that attack, I've realized it's something we must earn─all of us, working together.
Our training has prepared us for combat with monsters several times our size, but when it comes to mechanical soldiers armed with weapons we've never seen before...what are we meant to do?
We've completely changed the way we look at sparring. None of us want to see a single person cut down in front of us─not ever again.
How am I meant to protect my crops and my family at the same time...?
As soon as it's ready, this harvest is bound for Aunt Tii's. If you'd like to taste my produce at its freshest, you should swing by for a taco sometime!
At first I balked at the prospect of Gulool Ja Ja stepping down, but now I think we'll be just fine. Our little Wuk Lamat's all grown up...
We've scarcely had time to welcome our new rulers, and now this? Can't we have a day of peace in this damned country?
Ever since the rite of succession, it's been one thing after another... Well, thank the gods it's finally calmed down around here. I've had enough excitement for a lifetime!
You took part in the rite of succession, did you not? We have heard much of your endeavors. If you have business in Vollok Shoonsa, please, go right ahead.
In response to the attack, we have stepped up patrols and bolstered security. You and your compatriots, however, will always be welcome in the palace.
Until the Vow of Resolve returns, we shall defend Vollok Shoonsa with our lives. Rest assured that the palace will be safe in your absence.
Vollok Shoonsa lies beyond this gate. The Dawnservants will be delighted to receive you.
Greetings, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! How fares the hunt? Finding your way around Tural without incident, I hope?
Those machines─I've never seen anything like them. 'Twas all I could do just to guide the folks here to safety... How could I have been so unprepared?
To hunt is to live, and to live is to hunt. But your life is worth more than any mark, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Always remember that.
Beautiful, healthy plants, aren't they? Growing a garden on the coast has its challenges, but it's nothing we can't overcome.
It frightens me to think those soldiers might strike again... If something were to happen to me, who would tend the fields?
Now that the crisis has been settled, it's time I saw to the harvest. It's a miracle any of our vegetables made it through that attack unscathed...
Even as the Head of Reason takes his rest, the Wing of Reflection continues to work tirelessly for the sake of Tuliyollal.
Under the leadership of Dawnservant Koana, I pledge to do the utmost to aid our nation's progress.
Even in times of war, the Wing of Reflection has a role to play. Our most pressing job is ensuring the Vow of Resolve can concentrate on the fight ahead.
The Wing of Reflection must consider what it can do to support Tuliyollal in the coming years. I for one shall study the precedents of nations overseas, and help our Dawnservants forge their path.
First time in Tuliyollal? If nothing else, you simply must try the tacos. You won't find this flavor anywhere else!
The founding of our great nation was supposed to put an end to the war and bloodshed! We don't know how to fight─we weren't trained for this!
Finally, life is back to normal. Much and more has changed here in Tuliyollal, but I welcome it─just so long as our peace is preserved.
Aunt Tii's tacos are growing in popularity of late, but I always find myself returning to Xbalyav Ty'e. When it comes to food, perhaps I'm simply not the adventurous type.
Wuk Lamat comes here from time to time, just to grab a taco and chat with the ordinary folk like me. With her in charge, I daresay we're in good hands.
This isn't how I'd hoped to celebrate the crowning of our new Dawnservants. Hopefully it's resolved quickly...
Did you know Wuk Lamat came by the other day? I'm sure she was trying to be discreet, but we all heard her coming from malms away. Hee hee! She hasn't changed a bit.
I know I should evacuate, but if I leave now, all my hard-won business negotiations will fall through. I have to hold firm!
Now that the life-threatening peril has passed, it's time to resuscitate the economy by doing what I do best!
In this world, there are as many strategies as there are soldiers. To adapt to any given situation, one must train the mind to always think ahead.
I must admit, I never pictured Wuk Lamat as our new Vow of Resolve. When is Commander Zoraal Ja coming back, anyway?
This is what we've been training for! We must hold our ground and repel the invaders!
The worst of it may be behind us, but I won't be letting my guard down. Now more than ever, we must always be prepared to handle the unforeseen!
There was a huge commotion over at Solution Nine, and the sentries were attacking people. In other words, the army turned on those it was supposed to protect.
Who knows what'll happen next? Hate to say it, but the drink's the only thing stopping me from losing the plot altogether. Don't suppose you'd care to join me?
After what happened to Queen Sphene, I'm at a loss for words.
You know, she once came and spoke with me about fishing, with great interest. Even now, I can still see her face, clear as day.
Nasty business over at Solution Nine, with the sentries running amok like that. Thankfully, we've been spared anything of the sort here, but I can't help but worry...
What do you think will change once the young Gulool Ja takes to the throne?
For people like me, it's unlikely we'd find ourselves out of work, so I'm not worried about that. I do hope that he brings a bit of stability to the place, though.
As much as I'd prefer not to venture outside, my work here is the only reason I escaped the turmoil in Everkeep.
To think that my research could be linked in any way to such a catastrophe. I am considering my future very carefully indeed...
On a break, huh? Don't mind us, we were just chatting about the recent goings-on in Everkeep. It sounds like a guest of Queen Sphene's fought off a bunch of rampaging sentries.
What!? That was you!? In that case, you have my gratitude.
Time for a break, is it? We were just talking about this and that. So Gulool Ja will take the throne, with Wuk Lamat as his guardian, it seems.
Despite what some might say, I'm not too concerned about it. If he's anything like his grandfather Gulool Ja Ja, I'm sure things will work out. That Wuk Lamat seems a good sort, as well.
Even without Queen Sphene, all of the essential systems are operating as normal.
While our daily lives haven't faced much disruption, everyone seems rather on edge. At least, that's the impression I get from those in Everkeep whenever they place an order with us.
A friend of mine lives in Everkeep. We often ate vegetables together, but I haven't seen her since the disturbance.
The fact I can still remember her means she's alive, though she could be injured. Perhaps I should try paying her a visit.
Without Queen Sphene, things just aren't the same. Even the vegetables seem somewhat lifeless. Hmm... Perhaps I'm just imagining it?
A good proportion of the electrope mined here was for military use. Without that, there's no telling what will happen to this place.
It appears that two collector acquaintances of mine recently...ah, passed on. I asked around in Everkeep, but hardly anyone remembers them. It's just as I thought...
To suddenly lose all recollection of those you once knew... Doesn't that bother the people wearing regulators?
Is it true that we can go beyond the barrier? I would like nothing more than to free myself of this wretched lightning, but Yyasulani is my home.
I wonder if things have calmed down at Solution Nine? A game of Triple Triad would help settle the nerves, but I can't find anyone in Everkeep who knows how to play.
Have you seen what's become of Canal Town? I've never seen one of the terminals shut down before.
When my father finally joins me here in Living Memory, I had hoped to take him to a resort there. But now...
Yesterland has fallen silent, its vibrant lights snuffed out. \\<sigh> What a poor sight Living Memory has become.
I am glad my little sister is not here to witness this.
Did you see? Asyle Volcane has been shut down as well. It was a dream of mine to take my mother to the hot springs there, but now it can never be...
I thought if I waited here long enough, my family would eventually become Endless, and join me here in Living Memory. I realize the futility of it all, and yet a part of me cannot let go.
If you are indeed the one who shut down the other terminals, I beg you─shut down the main terminal as well. Free me from this longing, this heartache...
The Bergmähr-Ring is presently out of service. We apologize for the inconvenience, and thank you for your patience and understanding until operations resume.
Please do not be alarmed. The aether of all residents will shortly be replenished. I repeat, please do not be alarmed.
You're wondering how we direct our alpaca wagons without reins? Well, a trained alpaca can be commanded with tongue clicks and whistles.
Two sharp clicks means “hold up!” while blowing hard through pursed lips means “off you go!” You should try it!
Ever since the ascension ceremony, our mezcal is selling as fast as we can stock it! All day we hear the wagon drivers whistling for the alpacas to hurry along!
Have you been up the slope there? Take a look if you like, and see how the mezcal is made.
The new Dawnservants have quite the burden to bear, but the knowledge passed down to them by their father will surely see them through.
Now that peace has settled in, I believe the time has come to introduce xibruq pibil to Tuliyollal. I'm certain the people will love it!
Visitors are still rare in Mamook, so we have little opportunity to learn of the goings-on outside this forest. Our unwelcoming reputation persists, I'm afraid...
I'm so glad to hear that peace has returned to Tuliyollal. Wuk Lamat is a wonderful Dawnservant indeed.
A citizen who had dealings with the Landsguard told us of Tuliyollal's recent triumphs. The Dawnservant continues to prove what may be achieved by joining hands with others...
The recent escalations have reminded me of all we stand to lose to the senselessness of violence. Would that I had honored peace sooner...
Phew...
Now my workspace is just the way I like it, I have inspiration oozing from every pore! Think that lantern was nice? Just wait until my next masterpiece...
The Second and Third Promise are to rule jointly, or so I hear. I shall craft a magnificent gift to commemorate their ascension.
The helphands don't wish to disturb us, so they've tried keeping things quiet, but anyone with ears has heard the rumors of war in Tuliyollal. What's to become of the city...?
When I asked Rakorok how Tuliyollal fared, he said the enemy forces had retreated. I hope this means our people can gain the upper hand...
Even with everything that's happened, I've been able to craft safely here to my heart's content. I aim to show my gratitude for this daily blessing with every fine piece I create.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Rakorok sends the Third Promise many wellwishings for the contest! She has made Rakorok's helphanding job much easier!
Pfff... Kohhh... Rakorok will ask potsworn to craft commemorative gifts to celebrate thronesitting of new Dawnservants!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Rakorok hears that Tuliyollal came under siegefighting. Who would do such a thing!? And why!?
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Is it true the city drove off the fightyfoes? Three cheers for Dawnservant Koana!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Rakorok is glad that warfighting is over. Peace is best for everyone!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... This is no time for mettletests!
The helphands are frantic. The potpacts must be upheld!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Rediroq is most thankful for your help with the helphands. She cannot let it swaychange her impartiality as an elector, however!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... All the Promises earned their keystones. The children of Gulool Ja Ja have proven their mettleworth!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Where could the Third Promise be? I hope she wasn't grabsnatched or bitegobbled!
Pfff... Kohhh... Rediroq is glad the Third Promise is safe! But please, keep on your tippytoes─the testingtrials are not over yet.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Rediroq had her suspicions that the Head of Reason had passed... But he would be pleased to know that Koana has inherited his namerole.

I shall be cheering on Wuk Lamat from Earthenshire!
The Third Promise claimed the throne, just as she said she would. With such a shining example to follow, how can I pursue my craft with any less commitment?
Just when I'd found somewhere I could be myself again, the nation itself comes under attack. I cannot imagine why anyone would wish to destroy this peaceful way of life...
I've been anxious ever since Tuliyollal came under siege, but pitching in with the train modifications has done much to allay the worst of my fears. It feels good to do something to help!
We have dragons on our side? How in the name of the gods did that come about?
Even with the fighting over, there remains much to be done. This is my home now, and I intend to take every advantage of my potsworn privileges to help Tuliyollal recover from the conflict.
So, the rite of succession is upon us. I wonder which of the claimants will be our next Dawnservant...
The Third Promise led the hunting party which slew Valigarmanda!? My first impression of her could not have been more wrong.
All hail Wuk Lamat, the Vow of Resolve. Never will I forget the great debt we owe her─and her courageous allies─for ridding us of the Skyruin.
Word has reached us of an attack on the city. The Vow of Resolve will have her mettle tested in the days to come...
It is said our new Dawnservants repelled Tuliyollal's would-be invaders. Thus do they prove themselves worthy of their titles.

The wounds I suffered when the Skyruin broke free have fully healed at last. I am eternally grateful to you and your battle companions─had you not slain the tural vidraal, I likely would be suffering still.
I see you are curious about our traditional carvings. Please, keep your distance while I work─I wouldn't want you to be struck by an errant chip.
My skin no longer burns as it did when I first felt the sting of Valigarmanda's flames. That sensation was...most unpleasant.
When time permits, we shall have to carve a new pillar─a grand monument to the heroes who slew the Skyruin.
First Valigarmanda escapes, now Tuliyollal faces another menace...
Is it true that the flying ships have withdrawn from Tuliyollal? Whatever the reason, I am glad that no more people need fear being hurt or killed in the conflict.
The new Dawnservants and their allies have already vanquished the Skyruin and defeated an invasion. We may need several pillars to record these deeds in their entirety...
Ah... Now I must begin my count again. I would ask that you not disturb me.
The dryness in my throat has faded at last. It is proof that the Skyruin is no more.
I am organizing a cargo of goods to be sent to Tuliyollal in celebration of our new Dawnservants. We owe them our lives, and must take care to show the proper respect.
Flying ships attacking Tuliyollal...? Where have they come from?
I hear Tuliyollal's invaders have surrendered the skies above the city. The sibling rulers have done well in protecting their people from further harm.
Ah, the champion from across the salt. Rest assured that those harmed in the Skyruin's escape are much recovered from their injuries.
Ugh...
\\<groan>
Urgh...
Now that my duties as elector are fulfilled, I am free to witness the conclusion to the contest as an interested Tuliyollan and nothing more.
Long has it been since I visited Tuliyollal, yet while the city is pleasant enough, breathing this fresh mountain air is where I feel most at home...
That Gulool Ja Ja should survive a battle with Valigarmanda only to be struck down by his own son... Who could have foreseen such a tragic fate?
I went to see the damage done to the city, and helped clear away the larger chunks of rubble. After all, what good is the gift of my size if I do not put it to use in such times?
The Dawnservants did well to stand against an unfamiliar foe. Gulool Ja Ja will be watching over his successors with pride.
The Vow of Resolve has made her return. By all accounts, she is every ilm the daughter of Gulool Ja Ja.
Though we live longer than most peoples, never did I expect to see Valigarmanda slain in my lifetime...
After all the Second and Third Promises have done for Urqopacha, it is unthinkable that any here would oppose their ascension to the throne.
No sooner have the new Dawnservants been crowned than we have lost the great Gulool Ja Ja... Yet while his memory persists, then so shall he.
We have kept ourselves apart too long, and missed Tuliyollal's growth into a powerful nation.
The invaders inflicted serious wounds, but the Dawnservants are no strangers to trials. I have faith that they will overcome these hardships.
It's hard not to feel anxious, all things considered, but there's only so much we can do. I wish you luck, friend.
Oh, and uh... Thank you. For keeping Nitowikwe safe.
Nothing to worry about here. Thanks to Estinien, we've not a single wounded to speak of.
Seems the fighting's over, and we have you and yours to thank for it.
May have cost us a train, but we can always build another. And with input from Vow Koana, I'm sure it'll be a sight better than the last one.
Put some steel in my hands, and I'm sure there's more I could've done to help. Don't suppose you know if Vow Wuk Lamat would teach me how to use an axe, do you?

Glad to see you safe and sound, though to be honest, I'm not surprised. I know a survivor when I see one, and as long as that heart of yours is still beating, I know you'll do whatever it takes to pull through.
The Dawnblazer was amazing, wasn't it? There's no doubt in my mind it'll go down as one of the greatest trains in history!
The fighting was so intense! Ships were blasting us from the air, soldiers everywhere─it was absolute chaos!
Then Estinien appeared as if out of nowhere! He'd leap into the air, and next thing you knew, they were keeling over one after another.
I can hardly wait till we start building our next train.
Oh, I've got so many ideas! Maybe we can build one that can travel underwater. Or one that can fly!
Nitowikwe told us everything that happened. We were relieved to hear the plan went off without a hitch.
Estinien put on quite the show thrashing those weird metal soldiers. Zekowa and his friends were no slouches either. It's not every day you see such fine gunplay.
I understand Shenza's enthusiasm for a new train, but I wish he wouldn't get so carried away with all his ideas.
A shame you couldn't be here to see me gun down all those soldiers.
All in a day's work for the leader of the Daybreakers!
Estinien was something else. Put us to shame, if I'm to be completely honest. Still, it didn't stop the Daybreakers from doing our part!
Where there's wrongs that need to be righted, we'll be there!
Zekowa and Kwikana are awfully excited to finally be getting on with work. That isn't to say I'm not enthused myself, mind.
But we can't just run headlong into trouble like we used to. We'll need to cooperate with the Dustwatch if we want things done right.
The sky's finally clear of those ships, so it seems the danger's passed. For now, at least.
My officers'll tell you I have a carefree attitude on most days, but when there's trouble, I'll be there front and center.
Hhusatahwi owes you and your companions a great debt. Not only for helping against those mechanical monsters, but also that incident with the Vulture.
I'll be kicking myself for some time yet over that. Still, I'll learn from my mistakes and be a better officer for it.
I believe there's someone waiting for you.
You find those bandits and you beat 'em bloody, you hear?
I hope they get the train up and running soon.
One moment everything was fine, the next there's a giant dome off in the distance. And it looks like it's over Yyasulani...
What was it again...?
Nicely done finding that crystal. Won't be long now before the train's ready!
Oh, thank goodness you're safe.
We heard from Nitowikwe that everything went to plan, but I couldn't help but worry.
No need to worry about us. Thanks to Zekowa and that spear-wielding friend of his, everyone here is safe.
You be careful out there, you hear? And be sure to keep an eye on Elene'shpya and Cahciua for me.
Elene'shpya told me everything. About your fight inside the dome. His mother...
It's a relief to know that, even to the last, she never lost her inquisitive nature. She never gave up on her dream... And now it lives on in Elene'shpya.
My apologies for laughing earlier. Your friend painted an image so far removed from the Sphene we know, I couldn't help myself.
Honestly, I couldn't ask for a better job. Fresh air, and I get to spend most of my day with these darling rroneek.
I knew it! I knew Wuk Lamat would win the contest!
Who are these villains to attack Tuliyollal without warning or provocation!? This is unforgivable!
Tuliyollal is like the reed─we may bend in the storm but never break!
The fighting's over, then...? Even so, festival plans will need to wait while there's restoration work to be done.
Both Wuk Lamat and Koana greatly resemble Gulool Ja Ja in their own ways. More than ever, I am curious to behold the outcome of this contest.
In the end, it was not a two-head who took the throne, but two heads! Showing such wisdom, Wuk Lamat may become a greater Dawnservant than even Gulool Ja Ja!
Gulool Ja Ja served long and well... May he go now to his well-earned rest.
I don't know who these invaders are, but Tuliyollal will not easily fall. Gulool Ja Ja founded a resilient nation.
At first the rite of succession barely stirred my interest, but now I am eager to see how it unfolds...
Dawnservant Koana has also made remarkable growth upon his journey. Full glad am I to see the new importance he places on this nation's diverse cultures.
The audacity of those intruders! Rest assured that Wuk Evu will not stand idly by while such villains run amok!
That was the first time I witnessed one of Xak Tural's locomotives. Its self-propulsion was quite remarkable.

Tuliyollal has warded off all who would threaten her peace. From what I hear, even the tural vidraal may have risen to our defense─many spotted giant scaled creatures similar to Valigarmanda soaring through the skies in the heat of battle.
The fighting may have ended, but much still remains unresolved. That city of machines now fused with Xak Tural...how the Dawnservants choose to engage with it will be telling indeed.
Heading westward? I'll be sailing for Tuliyollal just as soon as my cargo's stowed.
Thanks to you, my work is almost done. All that's needed now is patience.
Thanks to the Third Promise and her mighty swings, we've collected some suitable logs of uyuipo. What of the abokixa?
Gah, bloody vehicles flying off all by themselves! Whoever's behind this is goin' to be sorry if I find them!
This vessel is bound for Old Sharlayan and will be departing momentarily.
Ever since I put on my neo regulator, I can feel the envious glances... But I ain't got much to offer anyone besides drinks.
I still hear them...the screams as that hover cargo came barreling through here. \\<sigh> Maybe a few drinks will drown them out.
One of our machines went out of control while we were working on it, but Monom shut it down in a flash. His quick thinking made me realize anew why he's the boss around here.
I can take you as far as Dock Tumu. Be sure to hold on tight!
We're currently offering support for those who wish to transfer their soul cells to neo regulators.

I gave the neo regulator I received at the funeral to my fiancée, so I came here to see if I could get another one for myself. They told me distribution had ended...right before chaos broke out. I barely escaped with my life...
I'm glad to have a neo regulator, but so many I know aren't as lucky. What is Queen Sphene thinking, limiting supply to only five thousand?
Tuliyollal, you say? I'd be happy to take you!
After a red-haired Hhetsarro took charge, it didn't take long for things to get tidied up. I wasn't able to do much, but I lent a hand where I could.
Come again any time.
I'm here to provide a peaceful place to relax over coffee. The people might be hurting now, but I hope here they can find comfort.
The Dawnservants have charged us with protecting the forest, and protect it we will.
The preparations continue at the Starlight Stalls. Will you be heading there?
Now that things have settled, I'm going to take another look at our data on Preservation.
Cahciua may no longer be with us, but you're always welcome here. We're all comrades now, and it's always a pleasure to see you.
Damn it all... What in the world is happening?
Say, you remember the energy tonic I gave you? On the can, there's a picture of a peculiar creature─a beaver-like thing.
I've never seen one in real life, but it's supposed to be downright ferocious. If an Arcadion fighter uses its soul, I wonder what they'd be able to do...
I'm glad me weapons were of use in the battle. But at the same time, I wish we didn't have need fer 'em...
Times like this, ye've got to keep yer hands movin'.
Hey, ye ever heard o' the Rhodina Consortium? I absolutely can't stand that lot, let me tell ye.
That's why I give the Nexus Arcade a wide berth. Even the residential district's too close fer me likin', so I just crash here.
We lent our hover cargo to your friends. Although I couldn't see what was happening, it was plain from the sounds that it was nothing good...
From the beginning, I had noticed that Queen Sphene's sound was different to ours.
But such things didn't matter. What mattered was that she was there for us, laughing when we laughed and crying when we cried.
I want to thank you on behalf of Oblivion. If it weren't for you, we couldn't have stopped Zoraal Ja and his army. I shudder to imagine how much worse the casualties might have been.
The others have also told us about Cahciua. After being so torn over what to tell her son, I'm glad she had the chance to bare her heart to him at the last.
Thank you so much for saving me. When I was caught, I had feared the worst...
The interference to our communications, we suspect, was caused by Queen Sphene. No one else could have done such a thing...
Shale tells us that my father's name was on the list of test subjects at Origenics.
Thank you. For freeing him from his suffering, and for getting justice for us.
I can't thank you enough for saving Wayakkwe. If something had happened to her, I don't know what I would do...
Oh, Shale sent word that she found data about our father in Origenics's system. She's promised to take a good look at it for us. Hopefully we'll learn something...
Even with the ascension ceremony over there is much to do! We have to ready our stock for the commemorative campaign.
This is hardly the time for peddling commemorative wares. We have to do what we can to help!
It's wonderful how the train turned out. I'm glad I could pitch in with procuring materials!
Tuliyollal will never fall! Not under our dependable Dawnservants, and not with allies like you at our side!
The fighting's over, but it's still not the time for peddling commemorative wares. A merchant like me can surely offer assistance of some kind.
To think that she would nominate her brother to be the Reason to her Resolve... Wuk Lamat is an interesting character, indeed.
Even those known for viewing war as opportunity have changed their tune since the city came under attack.
We were bringing supplies to Tuliyollal when we saw a great dragon soaring through the sky! It was almost as majestic as an alpaca in full canter!
It is a shame what became of the First Promise... Such a shame. As for the golden alpaca he left behind, I will take responsibility for its care and well-being.
The Third Promise impressed me with her bartering skills. She would be my pick for Dawnservant...if the Second Promise weren't in the running, of course.
So, Koana and Wuk Lamat will rule side by side. I am pleased─this is the best of both worlds!
We've had word that Tuliyollal came under attack. Perhaps a shipment of mate tea will aid in soothing weary bodies and spirits...
The warships have retreated, but as I saw during my mate delivery, people's fears do not so easily vanish. I pray they find peace of mind in the coming days.
